text: Nizhneulu-Yelga () is a rural locality (a selo) and the administrative center of Nizhneulu-Yelginsky Selsoviet, Yermekeyevsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 335 as of 2010. There are 3 streets. == Geography == It is located 4 km from Yermekeyevo. == References == Category:Rural localities in Yermekeyevsky District
title: Nizhneulu-Yelga
